#: src/introduction.md:5
msgid ""
"Onboarding-oriented documentation for new users and embedders. Where the "
"[architecture](../architecture/README.md), [spec](../spec/README.md), and "
"[reference](../reference/README.md) sections describe what Keleusma is, this "
"section describes how to use it."
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:10
msgid ""
"The guide is in two layers. The first is a linear course of forty chapters "
"that teaches Keleusma from scratch, sized for video presentation and ordered "
"as a single learning arc. The second is a set of reference pages for lookup "
"and deeper study. The course and the reference pages overlap by design: the "
"course is for first learning, the reference pages are for going back."
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:17
msgid "The Course"
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:19
msgid ""
"Forty chapters in ten parts. Each chapter is self-contained and demo-driven, "
"sized to roughly one short video. Parts I through VIII teach the language; "
"Part IX teaches embedding into a Rust host; Part X points onward."
msgstr ""

