#: src/GETTING_STARTED.md:5
msgid ""
"This document walks a new user through installing the Keleusma command-line "
"frontend, writing and running a first script, and embedding the same script "
"in a Rust host program. The walkthrough assumes a working Rust toolchain at "
"edition 2024 and minimum supported Rust version 1.88."
msgstr ""

#: src/GETTING_STARTED.md:7
msgid "Install the CLI"
msgstr ""

#: src/GETTING_STARTED.md:9
msgid ""
"Keleusma ships a standalone CLI binary called `keleusma`. The CLI provides a "
"script runner, a bytecode compiler, and an interactive REPL. Install it from "
"the workspace root."
msgstr ""

#: src/GETTING_STARTED.md:17
msgid "Verify the installation."
msgstr ""

#: src/GETTING_STARTED.md:23
msgid ""
"If the command is not found, ensure Cargo's bin directory is on the shell "
"`PATH`. The default location is `~/.cargo/bin`."
msgstr ""

#: src/GETTING_STARTED.md:25
msgid "A First Script"
msgstr ""

#: src/GETTING_STARTED.md:27
msgid "Create a file called `hello.kel` with the following contents."
msgstr ""

#: src/GETTING_STARTED.md:39
msgid "Run the script."
msgstr ""

#: src/GETTING_STARTED.md:45 src/GETTING_STARTED.md:137
msgid "Expected output."
msgstr ""

#: src/GETTING_STARTED.md:51
msgid ""
"The runner parses, compiles, verifies, and executes the script. Atomic total "
"functions declared with `fn` may not yield to the host or contain unbounded "
"recursion. The `main` function is the entry point. The return type appears "
"in the function signature and is required."
msgstr ""

#: src/GETTING_STARTED.md:53
msgid "Compile to Bytecode"
msgstr ""

#: src/GETTING_STARTED.md:55
msgid ""
"The CLI can serialize a script to bytecode. The serialized form is loadable "
"through the embedding API."
msgstr ""

#: src/GETTING_STARTED.md:61
msgid ""
"The output file uses the framed wire format with magic, length, version, "
"target word and address widths, body, and CRC trailer. A host loads the file "
"through `Vm::load_bytes`."
msgstr ""

#: src/GETTING_STARTED.md:63
msgid "Interactive REPL"
msgstr ""

#: src/GETTING_STARTED.md:65
msgid "Start the REPL to explore the language interactively."
msgstr ""

#: src/GETTING_STARTED.md:71
msgid ""
"The REPL accumulates declarations into a session prefix and evaluates "
"expressions against the current prefix. The REPL supports the colon-prefixed "
"commands `:help`, `:quit`, `:reset`, and `:show`."
msgstr ""

#: src/GETTING_STARTED.md:83
msgid ""
"The REPL wraps each expression as `fn main() -> T { <expression> }` and "
"tries return types `Word`, `Float`, `bool`, `Text`, and `()` in order. The "
"first type that compiles is used. Expressions whose type lies outside this "
"list require an explicit function declaration."
msgstr ""

#: src/GETTING_STARTED.md:85
msgid "Embed in a Rust Host"
msgstr ""

#: src/GETTING_STARTED.md:87
msgid ""
"The same script runs from a Rust host program. Create a new Cargo project."
msgstr ""

#: src/GETTING_STARTED.md:94
msgid "Add Keleusma to `Cargo.toml`."
msgstr ""

#: src/GETTING_STARTED.md:96
msgid ""
"```\n"
"[dependencies]\n"
"keleusma = \"0.2\"\n"
"keleusma-arena = \"0.3\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/GETTING_STARTED.md:102
msgid "Replace `src/main.rs` with the following."
msgstr ""

#: src/GETTING_STARTED.md:111
msgid ""
"\"\n"
"    fn double(x: Word) -> Word { x + x }\n"
"    fn main() -> Word { double(21) }\n"
"\""
msgstr ""

#: src/GETTING_STARTED.md:131
msgid "Build and run."
msgstr ""

#: src/GETTING_STARTED.md:143
msgid ""
"The host code performs the same compile-verify-run pipeline as the CLI "
"runner. The four steps are visible in the source: lex, parse, compile, and "
"execute. The `Arena` is the bounded-memory region the VM borrows for its "
"operand stack and dynamic-string allocations. `DEFAULT_ARENA_CAPACITY` is "
"sixty-four kilobytes, sufficient for most scripts and the value used by the "
"bundled examples."
msgstr ""

#: src/GETTING_STARTED.md:145
msgid "Next Steps"
msgstr ""

#: src/GETTING_STARTED.md:147
msgid ""
"The walkthrough above produces a running Keleusma host. Common next steps "
"include the following."
msgstr ""

#: src/GETTING_STARTED.md:149
msgid ""
"Read [EMBEDDING.md](./EMBEDDING.md) for the full embedding surface, "
"including native function registration, arena sizing, the call and resume "
"loop for stream-classified scripts, and error recovery."
msgstr ""

#: src/GETTING_STARTED.md:150
msgid ""
"Read [WHY_REJECTED.md](./WHY_REJECTED.md) when the verifier rejects a "
"program. The document maps error messages to root causes and proposes "
"rewrites."
msgstr ""

#: src/GETTING_STARTED.md:151
msgid ""
"Explore [`examples/scripts/`](../../examples/scripts) for short scripts "
"demonstrating common language features. Each script runs through `keleusma "
