#: src/METRICS.md:11
msgid ""
"**Binary size**: stripped or default release-build size as reported by `ls "
"-l`. Path resolved through `readlink` where present."
msgstr ""

#: src/METRICS.md:12
msgid ""
"**Maximum resident set size**: peak RSS as reported by `/usr/bin/time -l` on "
"macOS. Includes the runtime's own memory plus all shared libraries page-"
"resident at any point."
msgstr ""

#: src/METRICS.md:13
msgid ""
"**Peak memory footprint**: peak dirty + anonymous memory as reported by `/"
"usr/bin/time -l`. Lower than maximum RSS because it excludes shared library "
"text pages."
msgstr ""

#: src/METRICS.md:14
msgid ""
"**Cycles elapsed**: CPU cycles consumed from process start to process exit."
msgstr ""

#: src/METRICS.md:15
msgid ""
"**Real time**: wall-clock duration from process start to exit. Rounded to 10 "
"ms by the measurement tool."
msgstr ""

#: src/METRICS.md:17
msgid ""
"The Keleusma measurement runs the full strict-mode-capable CLI binary "
"including the encryption feature stack (X25519 + AES-256-GCM + HKDF-"
"SHA-256). The binary as measured is what an operator would deploy."
