#: src/LLM_USAGE.md:106
msgid "Scratch directories"
msgstr ""

#: src/LLM_USAGE.md:108
msgid ""
"Use `tmp/` for transient files (drafts, probe outputs, scratch scripts, "
"design specs awaiting integration). The contents of `tmp/` are gitignored by "
"convention and are never committed."
msgstr ""

#: src/LLM_USAGE.md:110
msgid ""
"A common AI reflex is to put work in the repository root or in a new "
"subdirectory of `docs/`. For draft material, `tmp/` is correct. For finished "
"material, the appropriate `docs/` subdirectory is correct. The pattern is: "
"drafts in `tmp/`, then promote to `docs/` once reviewed."
msgstr ""

#: src/LLM_USAGE.md:112
msgid "Useful prompt patterns"
msgstr ""

#: src/LLM_USAGE.md:114
msgid ""
"The patterns below produce higher-quality output than open-ended prompts."
msgstr ""

#: src/LLM_USAGE.md:116
msgid "The \"read first, summarise, then proceed\" pattern"
msgstr ""

#: src/LLM_USAGE.md:123
msgid ""
"The summarise-first step forces the AI to demonstrate that it actually read "
"the documents. It also gives the operator visible signal that the relevant "
"context was loaded."
msgstr ""

#: src/LLM_USAGE.md:125
msgid "The \"design before implementation\" pattern"
msgstr ""

#: src/LLM_USAGE.md:134
msgid ""
"For non-trivial work, design-before-implementation produces a reviewable "
"artefact and reduces the cost of changes-of-direction. The pattern is "
"established with `tmp/enrolled_keys_execution.md` and `tmp/"
"call_site_identifier.md` as worked examples."
msgstr ""

#: src/LLM_USAGE.md:136
msgid "The \"structural-bound\" pattern for algorithm work"
msgstr ""

#: src/LLM_USAGE.md:145
msgid ""
"Explicit reference to the work-stack pattern (or other Keleusma-specific "
"patterns) prevents the AI from defaulting to recursive Rust idioms."
msgstr ""

#: src/LLM_USAGE.md:147
msgid "The \"verify before claiming done\" pattern"
msgstr ""

#: src/LLM_USAGE.md:155
msgid ""
"Forces the AI to actually run the validation rather than claim success based "
"on inspection."
msgstr ""

#: src/LLM_USAGE.md:157
msgid "What this guide is not"
